mso-bidi-font-family:Verdana;color:white;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>In the <s=
pan
class=3DGramE>zoomed out</span> view ships and bases appear as circular ico=
ns.
The icons have the following meanings:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul style=3D'margin-top:0in' type=3Ddisc>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'color:white;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo3;tab-sto=
ps:list .5in'><span
     lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana",sans-seri=
f;
     mso-bidi-font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Blue icons: your
     empires ships and bases<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'color:white;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo3;tab-sto=
ps:list .5in'><span
     lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana",sans-seri=
f;
     mso-bidi-font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Yellow icons:
     neutral empires ships and bases<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'color:white;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo3;tab-sto=
ps:list .5in'><span
     lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana",sans-seri=
f;
     mso-bidi-font-family:Verdana;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Red icons: enemy
     empires ships and bases, or pirates<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'font-size:10.0pt;font-fami=
ly:"Verdana",sans-serif;
mso-bidi-font-family:Verdana;color:white;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'><o:p>&nbs=
p;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'font-size:10.0pt;font-fami=
ly:"Verdana",sans-serif;
mso-bidi-font-family:Verdana;color:white;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>In systems
that you control, your ships are not directly visible, only space ports and
fleets are visible in these situations. This minimizes the number of icons =
and
allows you to easily select the more important ships and bases when in the
zoomed-out sector view.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

